      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOKYO ROSE NZ (7) ran into a glamour mare but was far from disgraced when fourth in the Group 1 Queen of the Pacific at Melton last start. That was over 2760m so expect her to relish coming back to the mile having impressively won her previous two starts over the distance here. Can return to the winners' list. RIPPLES NZ (3) is a promising filly who was a Group 1 winner as a juvenile last season and made a winning start for Luke McCarthy when coming from a wide barrier to cruise home by 16.5m at this circuit and distance. This is stronger but she draws much lower and has plenty of upside. PRECISE NZ (6) draws deeper than when she placed in a higher-graded race last week but came from a wider barrier than this when scoring at this circuit and distance last month. GIPSY PRINCESS (5) was midfield as a hot favourite last start but had looked close to a win when recording a string of seconds prior so is worth another chance.",
